<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFBFFC4FF71FE09FB4DFD2B" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FE09FD82FE5B" blockId="19.[151,1437,438,645]" box="[151,639,474,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFBFFC4FF79FE09FF05FE5B" box="[159,248,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,198,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-32@66.[201,1387,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 13. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima sikhimensis group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605531/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 13</figureCitation>
: C–D, 20: I, 26: C–D, 32: A, 95: J)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FE2DFB4DFD2B" blockId="19.[151,1437,438,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
The forewings are reddish brown with green flecks like 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FCE6FE2DFC50FDB6" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[768,941,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mionopastea">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FCE6FE2DFC50FDB6" box="[768,941,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mionopastea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the inner margin is more deeply concave proximal to the tornal hook. The hindwing marginal band is closer to the outer margin and is more dentate at the veins than in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FECAFD95FE31FDCF" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[300,460,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikhimensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FECAFD95FE31FDCF" box="[300,460,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. sikhimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The forewing has a conspicuous greenish patch above the inner margin at the base and proximal to the PM line that is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FD86FDB9FD1CFD2A" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[608,737,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrannus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FD86FDB9FD1CFD2A" box="[608,737,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. tyrannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FCF1FDB9FC6BFD2A" baseAuthorityName="Banziger &amp; Honey" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[791,918,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantia">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FCF1FDB9FC6BFD2A" box="[791,918,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. aurantia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is found in 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FBDAFDB9FB50FD2B" box="[1084,1197,619,645]" name="Indonesia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
